    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Self-Refine: Same Model, Three Roles"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Self-Refine (Madaan et al., 2023) is an iterative refinement framework where a single LLM plays three roles in sequence: Generator (produces initial output), Feedback provider (critiques that output), and Refiner (applies the critique). Unlike Reflexion, which runs separate trials with episodic memory, Self-Refine improves a single output within one generation session using in-context feedback."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Self-Refine iterative loop",
          "title": ""
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Self-Refine demonstrates that a model can disagree with itself productively: generating an output, then switching roles to critique it, then switching again to fix the critique."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Core Data Structure"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import Optional\n\n@dataclass\nclass RefinementState:\n    task: str\n    current_output: str\n    feedback_history: list[str] = field(default_factory=list)\n    iteration: int = 0\n    stop_reason: Optional[str] = None\n\n    def add_iteration(self, feedback: str, refined_output: str) -> None:\n        self.feedback_history.append(feedback)\n        self.current_output = refined_output\n        self.iteration += 1\n\n    def history_context(self) -> str:\n        if not self.feedback_history:\n            return \"\"\n        lines = [\"Previous feedback rounds:\"]\n        for i, fb in enumerate(self.feedback_history):\n            lines.append(f\"  Round {i+1}: {fb[:120]}\")\n        return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Step 1 \u2014 Generate Initial Output"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The first call produces the initial output. This is a standard single-turn generation; the system prompt establishes the task and any constraints. Self-Refine has no special requirements on this step \u2014 any existing generation prompt works."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\ndef generate(\n    client: anthropic.Anthropic,\n    task: str,\n    system: str = \"You are a helpful assistant.\",\n) -> str:\n    resp = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=1024,\n        system=system,\n        messages=[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":task}],\n    )\n    return resp.content[0].text.strip()\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Step 2 \u2014 Provide Feedback"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The feedback step prompts the same model to critique its own output. The prompt explicitly asks for specific, actionable flaws \u2014 not general praise or vague suggestions. It also includes a stopping signal so the model can indicate when the output is already good."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "FEEDBACK_PROMPT = \"\"\"You are evaluating an output for the following task.\n\nTask: {task}\n\nOutput to evaluate:\n{output}\n\n{history}\n\nProvide specific, actionable feedback:\n- List each flaw as a bullet point\n- Be concrete: point to the exact line or claim that is wrong\n- If the output is already good enough, respond with exactly: STOP\n\nFeedback:\n\"\"\"\n\ndef get_feedback(\n    client: anthropic.Anthropic,\n    state: RefinementState,\n) -> str:\n    prompt = FEEDBACK_PROMPT.format(\n        task=state.task,\n        output=state.current_output,\n        history=state.history_context(),\n    )\n    resp = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=512,\n        messages=[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":prompt}],\n    )\n    return resp.content[0].text.strip()\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Step 3 \u2014 Refine the Output"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The refinement call receives the current output and the feedback, then produces an improved version. Crucially, the refiner sees both \u2014 not just the critique \u2014 so it can preserve the good parts of the original while fixing only what the feedback flagged."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "REFINE_PROMPT = \"\"\"You are improving an output based on feedback.\n\nTask: {task}\n\nCurrent output:\n{output}\n\nFeedback:\n{feedback}\n\nProduce a revised output that addresses every flaw in the feedback.\nKeep everything that is already correct. Do not introduce new issues.\n\nRevised output:\n\"\"\"\n\ndef refine(\n    client: anthropic.Anthropic,\n    state: RefinementState,\n    feedback: str,\n) -> str:\n    prompt = REFINE_PROMPT.format(\n        task=state.task,\n        output=state.current_output,\n        feedback=feedback,\n    )\n    resp = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=1024,\n        messages=[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":prompt}],\n    )\n    return resp.content[0].text.strip()\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Full Self-Refine Loop"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def self_refine(\n    client: anthropic.Anthropic,\n    task: str,\n    max_iterations: int = 3,\n    system: str = \"You are a helpful assistant.\",\n) -> RefinementState:\n    initial = generate(client, task, system)\n    state = RefinementState(task=task, current_output=initial)\n\n    for _ in range(max_iterations):\n        feedback = get_feedback(client, state)\n\n        if feedback.strip().upper() == \"STOP\":\n            state.stop_reason = \"model_satisfied\"\n            break\n\n        refined = refine(client, state, feedback)\n        state.add_iteration(feedback, refined)\n    else:\n        state.stop_reason = \"max_iterations\"\n\n    return state\n\n\n# Example usage\n# client = anthropic.Anthropic()\n# result = self_refine(\n#     client,\n#     task=\"Write a Python function that checks if a string is a valid email address.\",\n#     max_iterations=3,\n# )\n# print(f\"Final output after {result.iteration} iteration(s):\")\n# print(result.current_output)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Stopping Criteria"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The loop can stop in two ways: the model signals STOP in the feedback step (it is satisfied with the current output), or max_iterations is reached. A third option is an external quality gate \u2014 a test suite, linter, or external oracle \u2014 that overrides the model's self-assessment with ground truth."
          }
        ]
      },
